Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the Department of Agriculture in celebration of National Agriculture Day. He praised Secretary Sonny Perdue for his leadership and highlighted the importance of agriculture in America. Pence spoke about the advancements in technology and innovation in the agricultural industry and the role of American farmers in feeding the nation and the world. He emphasized the administration's commitment to supporting farmers through deregulation, tax cuts, and trade deals, and promised to continue working to advance American agriculture. Pence also acknowledged the contributions of the Department of Agriculture and its various agencies in supporting farmers and ensuring food safety. He concluded by expressing his confidence in the future of American agriculture and promising to make it great again.